Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_partition_wrapper(25.10)                create_partition_wrapper(25.10)

Name
       create_partition_wrapper  - Creates a wrapper partition that embeds the
       specified partition cell to preserve its verilog module  definition  in
       the netlist

Syntax
       create_partition_wrapper

       [-help]

       -partitions <partition_names>[-pushdown]

       [-wrapper_name <wrapper_suffix_string>]

       Creates a wrapper partition that embeds the specified partition cell to
       preserve its verilog module definition in the netlist. The wrapper par-
       tition  can  be  used  for  making netlist changes without changing the
       netlist of the embedded (wrapped) cell definition.

       The wrapper partition has the same partition definition  attributes  as
       the  specified  partition. The timing constraints (through SDC) and low
       power information (through UPF) of the  wrapper  partition  is  updated
       with  the correct hierarchical pin information. The pin constraints ap-
       plied on pins of the original partition are mapped to the  new  wrapper
       pins.

       Note:  After  the  wrapper partition is created using the create_parti-
       tion_wrapper command:

              * the original partition ceases to exist (deletePartition).

              * the fence attributes and pin constraints of the original  par-
                tition are removed.

              * the  module  pins  of the original partition as preserved such
                that they cannot be altered later.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each create_partition_wrapper parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man create_partition_wrapper

       -partitions <partition_names>
              Specifies  the name of one or more partitions on which the wrap-
              per is created.

              Note: The partition_wrapper will have the same:

              * Number, name and locations (If already assigned) of pins

              * Area, shape, location, orientation

              Data_type: string, optional

       -pushdown
              When enabled, it keeps the partition hinst intact for the  wrap-
              per partition.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -wrapper_name <wrapper_suffix_string>
              Specifies  the suffix that is added to a partition name for cre-
              ating a partition wrapper.

              Default: <ptnName>_wrapper

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command creates a wrapper partition with suffix wrap  for
       all the partitions in the design:

       create_partition_wrapper -partition * -wrapper_name wrap

